{"questionId":"19851","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math> the curve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;has a single local maximum.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> for which <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> has the smallest possible maximum value.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Value of local maximum&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi></msqrt></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>M1A1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>This has a minimum value when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[4 marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19851","referenceCode":"EXN.1.AHL.TZ0.15c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the value of a for which y ha